[ASSISTANT] To make an ExoPlayer fit the entire screen, you'll need to adjust the layout in your Android XML file and configure the ExoPlayer instance accordingly. Assuming you're working with an Android application, follow these steps:

1. **XML Layout File**:

   Open your XML layout file (usually located in `res/layout` directory) where you've defined the ExoPlayer view. Make sure the layout has enough space to accommodate the player.

   Example XML layout (activity_main.xml):

   ```xml
   <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
   <LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
       xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
       xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
       android:layout_width="match_parent"
       android:layout_height="match_parent"
       android:orientation="vertical"
       tools:context=".MainActivity">

       <com.google.android.exoplayer2.ui.PlayerView
           android:id="@+id/exoPlayerView"
           android:layout_width="match_parent"
           android:layout_height="match_parent"
           app:use_controller="true"
           app:resize_mode="fill"
           app:show_timeout="0"
           app:controller_layout_id="@layout/custom_controller_layout" />
   </LinearLayout>
   ```

   In the above example, `PlayerView` is set to match the parent's width and height.

2. **Configure ExoPlayer in Your Activity**:

   In your Activity or Fragment, you will need to configure the ExoPlayer instance and bind it to the `PlayerView`.

   Example (MainActivity.java):

   ```java
   import com.google.android.exoplayer2.SimpleExoPlayer;
   import com.google.android.exoplayer2.source.MediaSource;
   import com.google.android.exoplayer2.upstream.DefaultDataSourceFactory;
   import com.google.android.exoplayer2.upstream.DataSource;

   // ...

   SimpleExoPlayer player;
   PlayerView playerView;

   @Override
   protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
       super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
       setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);

       // Initialize player
       player = new SimpleExoPlayer.Builder(this).build();

       // Bind player to PlayerView
       playerView = findViewById(R.id.exoPlayerView);
       playerView.setPlayer(player);

       // Prepare media source (e.g., from a URL or local file)
       DataSource.Factory dataSourceFactory = new DefaultDataSourceFactory(this, "your_user_agent");
       MediaSource mediaSource = new ProgressiveMediaSource.Factory(dataSourceFactory)
               .createMediaSource(Uri.parse("http://example.com/your_video.mp4"));

       player.prepare(mediaSource);
   }

   @Override
   protected void onDestroy() {
       super.onDestroy();
       player.release(); // Release player resources
   }
   ```

3. **Resize Mode**:

   Make sure that `resize_mode` is set to `"fill"` in the XML layout. This ensures that the video will fill the entire `PlayerView`.

   ```xml
   app:resize_mode="fill"
   ```

4. **Handle Screen Rotation (Optional)**:

   If you want to handle screen rotation, you may need to save and restore the player's state during configuration changes (e.g., screen rotation). You can do this by overriding `onSaveInstanceState()` and `onRestoreInstanceState()`.

   ```java
   @Override
   protected void onSaveInstanceState(Bundle outState) {
       super.onSaveInstanceState(outState);
       playerView.getPlayer().release(); // Release player before saving state
   }

   @Override
   protected void onRestoreInstanceState(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
       super.onRestoreInstanceState(savedInstanceState);
       // Re-initialize player and set it back to PlayerView
       player = new SimpleExoPlayer.Builder(this).build();
       playerView.setPlayer(player);

       // Restore media source and other configurations
       DataSource.Factory dataSourceFactory = new DefaultDataSourceFactory(this, "your_user_agent");
       MediaSource mediaSource = new ProgressiveMediaSource.Factory(dataSourceFactory)
               .createMediaSource(Uri.parse("http://example.com/your_video.mp4"));

       player.prepare(mediaSource);
   }
   ```

